70.2	%C3%89mile_Zola	Émile Zola	Émile François Zola (French pronunciation: ; 2 April 1840 – 29 September 1902) was a French writer, the most important exemplar of the literary school of naturalism and an important contributor to the development of theatrical naturalism. He was a major figure in the political liberalization of France and in the exoneration of the falsely accused and convicted army officer Alfred Dreyfus, which is encapsulated in the renowned newspaper headline J'Accuse.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/ZOLA_1902B.jpg/220px-ZOLA_1902B.jpg
